{
  "texts": [
    "As with the Plummer lens, it is easy to verify that the mean κ within a disk of radius θ E is unity.",
    "Hence θ E really is the Einstein radius.",
    "The lens potential and deflection are extraordinarily simple:",
    "The deflection angle is simply θ E times the radial unit vector.",
    "The deflection angle always having the same magnitude θ E is the lensing analog of the circular speed being the same everywhere."
  ]
}